12 ROS 2 - Custom msg and srv

  • Open a terminal and run:
cs

ros2 pkg create --build-type ament_cmake tutorial_interfaces
  • In the same terminal and run:
cd tutorial_interfaces

mkdir msg srv

cd msg

touch Num.msg
  • In the same terminal and run:
code Num.msg
  • Add this line and save and close it:
int64 num

  • In the same terminal and run:
touch Sphere.msg

code Sphere.msg
  • Add this line ,save and close it:
geometry_msgs/Point center
float64 radius

  • In the same terminal and run:
cd  ../srv

touch AddThreeInts.srv

  • In the same terminal and run:
code AddThreeInts.srv
  • Add this line and save and close it:
int64 a
int64 b
int64 c
---
int64 sum

  • In the same terminal and run:
cd  ../srv

touch AddThreeInts.srv

In the same terminal and run:

code AddThreeInts.srv

Add this line and save and close it:

int64 a
int64 b
int64 c
---
int64 sum

  • In the same terminal and run:
cd ..

code CMakeLists.txt
  • You must add these lines  before the line if(BUILD_TESTING) ,save and close it:
find_package(geometry_msgs REQUIRED)

find_package(rosidl_default_generators REQUIRED)

rosidl_generate_interfaces(${PROJECT_NAME}

  "msg/Num.msg"

  "msg/Sphere.msg"

  "srv/AddThreeInts.srv"

  DEPENDENCIES geometry_msgs # Add packages that above messages depend on, in this case geometry_msgs for Sphere.msg

In the same terminal and run:

code package.xml

within the <package> element of package.xml ,save and close it:

<depend>geometry_msgs</depend>
<buildtool_depend>rosidl_default_generators</buildtool_depend>
<exec_depend>rosidl_default_runtime</exec_depend>
<member_of_group>rosidl_interface_packages</member_of_group>

  • In the same terminal and run:
cb

sb
  • Open another terminal and run:
ros2 interface show tutorial_interfaces/msg/Num

-Open another terminal and run:

ros2 interface show tutorial_interfaces/msg/Sphere

  • In the same terminal and run:
ros2 interface show tutorial_interfaces/srv/AddThreeInts

Exercise

  • Modify the publisher/subscriber package created in a previous lecture. changing the standard string msg to Num.msg that you have created.

Tips

  • Remember to add this line in Package.xml:
<exec_depend>tutorial_interfaces</exec_depend>

Reference : https://docs.ros.org/en/humble/Installation.html
